Class ProtocolConfig<T>

java.lang.Object
  net.ddns.mucaho.jnetrobust.ProtocolConfig<T>
Type Parameters:
T - the user data type
public class ProtocolConfig<T>
extends java.lang.Object

Configuration class which will be used to configure a protocol instance.

Default configuration values are provided, but can/should be changed if needed.

getPacketQueueTimeout

public long getPacketQueueTimeout()
Gets a number indicating the maximum time (in ms) unacked or unordered packaged user-data can stay in the internal queue until it can be resolved. A negative number indicates that the time should not be checked. Defaults to a negative number.

Returns:
the packet queue timeout

shouldRetransmit

public boolean shouldRetransmit()
Gets a boolean indicating whether the protocol should retransmit data. Defaults to true. If this setting is changed to false, more "aggressive" values should be set for packetOffsetLimit (e.g. 16) and packetQueueLimit (e.g. 16).

Returns:
boolean whether to retransmit or not

setShouldRetransmit

public void setShouldRetransmit(boolean shouldRetransmit)
Sets a boolean indicating whether the protocol should retransmit data. Defaults to true. If this setting is changed to false, more "aggressive" values should be set for packetOffsetLimit (e.g. 16) and packetQueueLimit (e.g. 16).

Parameters:
shouldRetransmit - boolean whether to retranmit or not
